Next Steps:
1. Immediately isolate the compromised web server
2. Identify the specific webshell file being used to execute commands
3. Analyze the commands executed to understand attacker objectives
4. Check for credential harvesting, lateral movement, and data staging
5. Scan the entire web directory for additional webshells
6. Review how the webshell was initially deployed
7. Perform full forensic analysis and incident response
