5. Remove the malicious plist file and associated executables
6. Check for other LaunchAgent/LaunchDaemon persistence on the system
', '["https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1543/001/","https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/macos/process_creation/proc_creation_macos_persistence_via_plistbuddy.yml"]', 'contains("log.eventMessage", "PlistBuddy") &&
contains("log.eventMessage", "RunAtLoad") &&
contains("log.eventMessage", ["LaunchAgents", "LaunchDaemons"])
', '2026-02-09 16:52:22.367111', true, false, 'origin', null, '[]', '["adversary.host","adversary.user"]');
insert into public.utm_correlation_rules (id, rule_name, rule_confidentiality, rule_integrity, rule_availability, rule_category, rule_technique, rule_description, rule_references_def, rule_definition_def, rule_last_update, rule_active, system_owner, rule_adversary, rule_deduplicate_by_def, rule_after_events_def, rule_group_by_def) values (467, 'Privacy Preferences (TCC) Database Tampering', 3, 3, 1, 'Privilege Escalation, Defense Evasion', 'T1548 - Abuse Elevation Control Mechanism', 'Detects unauthorized modifications to the macOS TCC (Transparency, Consent, and Control) database which controls application privacy permissions. The TCC database manages access permissions for sensitive resources like camera, microphone, location services, and file system access. Unauthorized modifications to this database can allow malicious applications to bypass privacy controls and gain access to sensitive user data.

Next Steps:
1. Investigate the process that modified the TCC database and verify if it''s authorized
2. Check what specific permissions were modified in the TCC database
3. Review recent application installations and permission requests
4. Examine system logs for other suspicious activities around the same timeframe
5. Verify the integrity of system privacy settings and restore from backup if necessary
6. Consider implementing additional monitoring for TCC database access
', '["https://www.huntress.com/blog/full-transparency-controlling-apples-tcc","https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1548/"]', '(contains("log.eventMessage", "Update Access Record:") && equals("log.subsystem", "com.apple.TCC")) ||
(equals("log.process", "sqlite3") && contains("log.eventMessage", "TCC.db")) ||
(equals("log.process", "tccutil") && contains("log.eventMessage", "reset")) ||
(contains("log.eventMessage", "TCC") && contains("log.eventMessage", "INSERT")) ||
(contains("log.eventMessage", "TCC") && contains("log.eventMessage", "UPDATE")) ||
(contains("log.eventMessage", "TCC") && contains("log.eventMessage", "DELETE")) ||
(equals("log.subsystem", "com.apple.TCC") && equals("log.category", "access") && contains("log.eventMessage", "modification"))
', '2026-02-09 16:52:22.610159', true, false, 'origin', null, '[]', '["adversary.host","adversary.user"]');
insert into public.utm_correlation_rules (id, rule_name, rule_confidentiality, rule_integrity, rule_availability, rule_category, rule_technique, rule_description, rule_references_def, rule_definition_def, rule_last_update, rule_active, system_owner, rule_adversary, rule_deduplicate_by_def, rule_after_events_def, rule_group_by_def) values (468, 'macOS Root Account Enabled', 3, 3, 2, 'Privilege Escalation', 'T1078 - Valid Accounts', 'Detects the execution of dsenableroot to enable the root account on macOS. The root account is disabled by default on macOS for security. Enabling it grants the highest level of system privileges and is commonly done by attackers for privilege escalation and persistent elevated access.

Next Steps:
1. Verify if the root account activation was authorized by IT administration
2. Identify the user and process that ran dsenableroot
3. Disable the root account immediately if unauthorized (dsenableroot -d)
4. Check for unauthorized logins using the root account
5. Review the system for other privilege escalation or persistence mechanisms
6. Audit sudo and su usage on the affected system
', '["https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1078/","https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/macos/process_creation/proc_creation_macos_dsenableroot_enable_root_account.yml","https://support.apple.com/en-us/102367"]', 'contains("log.eventMessage", "dsenableroot") &&
!contains("log.eventMessage", "-d")
', '2026-02-09 16:52:22.742585', true, false, 'origin', null, '[]', '["adversary.host","adversary.user"]');
