Next Steps:
1. Identify the internal host using DoH
2. Determine if DoH usage is authorized by organization policy
3. Check if the host has DNS-related malware or unauthorized DNS tools
4. Review if corporate DNS policies are being bypassed
5. Consider blocking known DoH resolver IPs at the perimeter
6. Investigate the host for other signs of compromise if DoH usage is unexpected
', '["https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1071/004/","https://www.cisco.com/en/US/technologies/tk648/tk362/technologies_white_paper09186a00800a3db9.html"]', 'exists("origin.ip") &&
