Next Steps:
1. Identify the user who accessed the IPFS phishing page
2. Check if the user submitted credentials on the phishing page
3. If credentials were submitted, immediately reset the affected account password
4. Enable MFA on the affected account if not already active
5. Check for unauthorized access to the user''s account from unusual locations
6. Block IPFS gateway domains at the proxy if not business-required
7. Review email logs for the phishing message that delivered the IPFS link
8. Report the IPFS phishing content to the gateway provider
', '["https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1056/","https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/web/proxy_generic/proxy_susp_ipfs_cred_harvest.yml","https://www.trustwave.com/en-us/resources/blogs/spiderlabs-blog/ipfs-abuse-in-phishing-campaigns/"]', 'equals("log.eventType", "http") &&
exists("origin.ip") &&
(
  (contains("log.http.hostname", "ipfs.io") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "cloudflare-ipfs.com") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "gateway.ipfs.io") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "dweb.link") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "ipfs.eth.aragon.network") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "cf-ipfs.com") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "gateway.pinata.cloud") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "ipfs.infura.io") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "ipfs.fleek.co") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "nftstorage.link") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", "w3s.link") ||
   contains("log.http.hostname", ".ipfs.") ||
   contains("log.http.url", "/ipfs/") ||
   contains("log.http.url", "/ipns/")
  ) &&
  (
    regexMatch("log.http.url", "(?i)(email|mail|e-mail|user|login|account)=") ||
    regexMatch("log.http.url", "(?i)#.*@.*\\.(com|org|net|edu|gov)")
  )
)
