Next Steps:
1. Identify the internal host generating the suspicious JA3 fingerprint
2. Review the JA3 hash against known malware fingerprint databases
3. Investigate the process making the TLS connection
4. Check if the JA3 matches known C2 frameworks (Cobalt Strike, Metasploit, Empire)
5. Scan the host for malware
6. Block or monitor connections with the identified JA3 fingerprint
