Next Steps:
1. Identify the internal host downloading the file
2. Review the file hash against threat intelligence databases
3. Check if the download was initiated by user action or automated
4. Quarantine or delete the downloaded file if confirmed malicious
5. Scan the host for additional malware or compromise indicators
6. Block the source domain/IP and investigate the delivery mechanism
