Next Steps:
1. Investigate the source IP for SSH brute force patterns
2. Check if SSH tunneling is being used to bypass network controls
3. Review SSH key-based authentication for unauthorized keys
4. Check for SSH connections to unusual internal or external destinations
5. Review the SSH client version for known vulnerable or suspicious clients
6. Consider restricting SSH access to authorized jump hosts only
', '["https://suricata.readthedocs.io/en/latest/rules/ssh-keywords.html","https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1021/004/"]', 'equals("log.eventType", "alert") &&
