3. Check for other discovery commands from the same user or host
4. Review if the user subsequently accessed resources in trusted domains
5. Correlate with other reconnaissance activities (BloodHound, SharpHound)
6. Monitor for lateral movement into discovered trusted domains
7. Review trust configurations for unnecessary or overly permissive trusts
', '["https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1482/","https://adsecurity.org/?p=1588","https://www.harmj0y.net/blog/redteaming/a-guide-to-attacking-domain-trusts/"]', '(equals("log.eventCode", "4688") || equals("log.eventCode", "1")) &&
(
  (regexMatch("log.winlog.event_data.CommandLine", "(?i)nltest(.exe)?\\s+/(domain_trusts|trusted_domains|dclist|dsgetdc)") ||
   regexMatch("log.winlogEventDataCommandLine", "(?i)nltest(.exe)?\\s+/(domain_trusts|trusted_domains|dclist|dsgetdc)")) ||
  (regexMatch("log.winlog.event_data.CommandLine", "(?i)dsquery(.exe)?\\s+trust") ||
   regexMatch("log.winlogEventDataCommandLine", "(?i)dsquery(.exe)?\\s+trust")) ||
  (regexMatch("log.winlog.event_data.CommandLine", "(?i)Get-ADTrust|Get-DomainTrust|Get-ForestTrust|Get-NetForestTrust") ||
