endpoint to authenticate on another. The rule monitors for Kerberos authentication events
(Event ID 4624 LogonType 3 with Kerberos package) combined with anomalous ticket usage
patterns and tools like Rubeus, Mimikatz kerberos::ptt, and Invoke-Mimikatz.

Next Steps:
1. Identify the source of the Kerberos ticket and the target system
2. Check if the ticket was exported using Mimikatz or Rubeus
3. Verify if the original ticket owner''s host is compromised
4. Review Kerberos TGS/TGT events from the source IP
5. Force Kerberos ticket renewal by resetting the user''s password
6. Check for additional lateral movement from the authenticated session
7. Implement Kerberos constrained delegation and armoring
', '["https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1550/003/","https://adsecurity.org/?p=2011","https://www.sans.org/blog/kerberos-in-the-crosshairs-golden-tickets-silver-tickets-mitm-and-more/"]', '(
  (equals("log.eventCode", "4688") || equals("log.eventCode", "1")) &&
  (
    (regexMatch("log.winlog.event_data.CommandLine", "(?i)kerberos::ptt") ||
     regexMatch("log.winlogEventDataCommandLine", "(?i)kerberos::ptt")) ||
    (regexMatch("log.winlog.event_data.CommandLine", "(?i)Rubeus.*ptt") ||
     regexMatch("log.winlogEventDataCommandLine", "(?i)Rubeus.*ptt")) ||
    (regexMatch("log.winlog.event_data.CommandLine", "(?i)Rubeus.*(asktgt|asktgs|renew|s4u|createnetonly)") ||
     regexMatch("log.winlogEventDataCommandLine", "(?i)Rubeus.*(asktgt|asktgs|renew|s4u|createnetonly)")) ||
    (regexMatch("log.winlog.event_data.CommandLine", "(?i)Invoke-Mimikatz.*kerberos") ||
     regexMatch("log.winlogEventDataCommandLine", "(?i)Invoke-Mimikatz.*kerberos")) ||
    (regexMatch("log.winlog.event_data.CommandLine", "(?i)klist.*purge|klist.*tickets") ||
     regexMatch("log.winlogEventDataCommandLine", "(?i)klist.*purge|klist.*tickets"))
  )
) ||
(
  equals("log.eventCode", "4768") &&
  equals("log.winlogChannel", "Security") &&
  !equals("log.winlog.event_data.Status", "0x0") &&
  oneOf("log.winlog.event_data.Status", ["0x1f", "0x20", "0x25"]) &&
  exists("log.winlog.event_data.IpAddress")
)
', '2026-02-09 16:55:33.357311', true, false, 'origin', null, '[]', '["adversary.host","adversary.user"]');
insert into public.utm_correlation_rules (id, rule_name, rule_confidentiality, rule_integrity, rule_availability, rule_category, rule_technique, rule_description, rule_references_def, rule_definition_def, rule_last_update, rule_active, system_owner, rule_adversary, rule_deduplicate_by_def, rule_after_events_def, rule_group_by_def) values (612, 'PetitPotam NTLM Relay Attack Detection', 3, 3, 2, 'Credential Access', 'T1187 - Forced Authentication', 'Detects PetitPotam NTLM relay attacks that abuse EFS RPC calls to coerce domain controller
authentication. The attack forces a DC to authenticate to an attacker-controlled host, enabling
NTLM relay to Active Directory Certificate Services (AD CS) for domain compromise. The rule
monitors Event ID 5145 (network share access) for IPC$ share access to specific EFS-related
named pipes used by PetitPotam.

Next Steps:
1. Identify the source IP attempting the EFS pipe access
2. Check if the source is an authorized system or a potential attacker
3. Verify if AD CS is configured and potentially vulnerable to NTLM relay
4. Apply Microsoft patches for PetitPotam (KB5005413)
5. Enable Extended Protection for Authentication on AD CS
6. Disable NTLM authentication where possible
7. Monitor for certificate enrollment from the relayed authentication
8. Restrict access to EFS RPC endpoints via Windows Firewall rules
', '["https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1187/","https://github.com/topotam/PetitPotam","https://msrc.microsoft.com/update-guide/vulnerability/ADV210003"]', 'equals("log.eventCode", "5145") &&
equals("log.winlogChannel", "Security") &&
equals("log.winlog.event_data.ShareName", "\\\\*\\IPC$") &&
(
  contains("log.winlog.event_data.RelativeTargetName", "efsrpc") ||
  contains("log.winlog.event_data.RelativeTargetName", "lsarpc") ||
  contains("log.winlog.event_data.RelativeTargetName", "efsr") ||
  contains("log.winlog.event_data.RelativeTargetName", "samr")
)
', '2026-02-09 16:55:33.503148', true, false, 'origin', null, '[{"indexPattern":"v11-log-wineventlog-*","with":[{"field":"log.winlogEventDataIpAddress","operator":"filter_term","value":"{{log.winlogEventDataIpAddress}}"}],"or":null,"within":"now-5m","count":3}]', '["lastEvent.log.winlogEventDataIpAddress","adversary.host"]');
